title: Essentials of Quantum Physics
narrative:
Essentials of Quantum Physics

Dianne Wilson PhD


This is a core requirements class for Physics majors and consists of 3 levels, Essentials, Intemediate, and Advanced

It is designed as follows:

  1. Ten quizzes per semeter comprising 50% of the grade
  2. Two page thesis 25% of the grade
  3. One final exam 25% of the grade

Students are expected to participate in discussions and show some aptitude for this discipline. Check with your class sponsor for associated paraphernalia.

title: General Principles of Artifical Intelligence and its Application
English as a Second Language 101
narrative:
This course is designed for those students whose mother tongue is Swahili. It will take you through the whole process of learning how to speak dialect free. Here are the main steps:

  1. understand basic clicks and tongue manipulation
  2. provide interactive learning tools and techniques
  3. writing and reading strategies to provide a rich array of skills
